The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 07, 2003 				 E-mail link for Orange, Hutch users 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Aug. 6: MSN India will offer MSN Messenger  the popular instant messenger service  on the cellphones of all Hutch subscribers in Calcutta, Chennai, Delhi, Karnataka, Gujarat and Andhra Pradesh and Orange users in Mumbai.																								MSN mobile hotmail will allow Hutch/Orange users to receive and send mail from their mobile phones.																								Similarly, the MSN mobile messenger will enable all Hutch/Orange users to check when their contacts are online and to instantly send and receive messages via a two-way short messaging service (SMS). This will work on every handset.																								The new service enables Hutch and Orange users to maintain constant contact with friends, family and colleagues, even when away from their PCs.																								MSN Mobile Hotmail offers, for the first time in India, superior filters that allow subscribers to carefully define what mails and messages they would like to receive on their mobile devices. 
